  <sect1 id="installation.video-hardware-specifications">
    <title>Video Hardware Specifications</title>
    <sect2 id="installation.graphic-card">
      <title>Graphic Card</title>
      <para>The graphic card will manage your video output. The
      choice of your graphic card will depend on how you want to
      use &app;. For now, we only support nvidia video card.
      Some ATI cards have problems with Xvideo extension. Before
      choosing your graphic card, determine on wich linux
      distribution and releases you are. Some graphic card may work
      only on certain releases. Before buying a graphic card,
      verify on the nvidia unix page that the hardware you are
      planning to use is supported not only by your linux
      distribution but also on the release you are using.
      </para>
      <para>We need to define the type of video output you will
      need. Usually this output is sent to a video mixer, a video
      projector, a monitor or any video display. On the table below
      we list the various possible ouput on a graphic card.
      </para>
      <table>
        <title>Graphic Card Output Types</title>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Video Output</entry>
              <entry>Determine the number and type of video output
              required</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>VGA</entry>
              <entry>The lowest common denominator that all PC
              graphics hardware supports</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>DVI</entry>
              <entry>video interface for digital display devices such as flat panel LCD computer displays and digital projectors</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>S-Video</entry>
              <entry>An analog video signal connection usually used to connect TV, DVD-Player or video mixer</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>HDMI</entry>
              <entry>Not supported and not tested yet</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
